Finra’s Ketchum Plans Cases Against Financial Firms, NYT Says

-- B y   J a m e s   K r a u s
-- 
2011-04-26T04:09:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/finra-s-ketchum-plans-cases-against-financial-firms-nyt-says.html
Richard G. Ketchum, chairman and
chief executive of the Financial Industry Regulatory Authority,
is challenging the Securities and Exchange Commission’s role for
enforcement of oversight of investment advisers, the New York
Times reported.  Ketchum has also overhauled the authority’s enforcement
division and plans to bring new cases against big Wall Street
firms as well as smaller ones, the newspaper reported.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
